1. A job candidate has years of experience, a diploma level, a count of required skills they possess, and a language proficiency level.
2. A candidate qualifies for an interview when they have at least three years of experience, at least a bachelor-equivalent diploma, at least six of the ten required skills, and a language proficiency of B2 or higher.
3. When qualified, the candidate's priority score is computed from their profile so that approved candidates can be ranked.
4. When refused, the first failing criterion is reported verbatim as the explicit reason for the refusal.
